{"type":"message","id":"a13592f2","parentId":"be7dc479","timestamp":"2026-03-24T02:21:41.317Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user doesn't want to use OpenAI with an API key. They probably want to use it differently - maybe through Ollama's OpenAI-compatible API, or they just want to use Ollama locally without OpenAI at all. Let me clarify what they want.\n\nActually, re-reading: \"Me gustaria configurar openapi y ollama para hacer un mejor uso de los tokens\" - they said \"openapi\" not \"openai\". Maybe they meant the OpenAI-compatible API that Ollama exposes? That would make sense for \"mejor uso de los tokens\" (better use of tokens) - route cheaper tasks to local models.\n\n\nSo they want to set up Ollama's local OpenAI-compatible endpoint to handle certain tasks and preserve their Anthropic token budget. I should look into how to configure this properly.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Entendido â€” nada de OpenAI cloud. Todo local con Ollama.\n\nOllama ya expone un endpoint compatible con la API de OpenAI en `http://localhost:11434`. Veamos cĂłmo configurar OpenClaw para aprovechar eso:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_01CQ5YtnQ1kcjyrTKiVjpUXY","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw status 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-opus-4-6","usage":{"input":3,"output":372,"cacheRead":19032,"cacheWrite":479,"totalTokens":19886,"cost":{"input":0.000015000000000000002,"output":0.009300000000000001,"cacheRead":0.009516,"cacheWrite":0.0029937500000000003,"total":0.02182475}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774318890475,"responseId":"msg_01PD9ZVNEvtQimfh8wjHsH3j"}}
